## Rules (never break these)

### Theme-first — single source of truth
All colors and fonts are defined once in `globals.css` (CSS variables) and
`tailwind.config.ts`. Changing the theme in those two files updates the entire
app. **Any hardcoded value breaks this contract.**

```tsx
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — hardcoded, breaks theming
<p style={{ color: '#484554', fontFamily: 'Inter' }}>
<div className="text-[#1a1c1e] bg-[#eeeef0] font-['Plus_Jakarta_Sans']">
<div className="text-gray-900 bg-gray-100">

// ✅ REQUIRED — semantic tokens, theme-aware
<p className="text-muted-foreground font-label">
<div className="text-foreground bg-surface font-sans">
```

- ❌ No arbitrary color values: `bg-[#fff]`, `text-[#333]`.
- ❌ No arbitrary font values: `font-['Inter']`, `font-['Plus_Jakarta_Sans']`.
- ❌ No inline `style={{}}` for colors, fonts, or spacing.
- ❌ No Tailwind generic palette: `text-gray-*`, `bg-slate-*`, `text-zinc-*` — always use semantic tokens.
- ✅ Mobile-first: base classes for 375px+, `md:` for ≥768px.
- ✅ Touch targets: interactive elements must have `min-h-touch` (44px) or `min-h-btn` (48px).
- ✅ All shadcn components inherit these tokens automatically via CSS variables.
